      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:MNOVH2014">Nakanishi and von Hinüber 2014</ref>. Because it mentions a cornice element, and because the upper pradakṣiṇapatha was only added in Phase III of the stūpa’s construction around 120 CE according to an inscription (<ref target="in:KanA8">KanA8</ref>), this inscription probably dates to around that time.</p>
	<p>See inscription <ref target="in:KanB2-24">KanB2-24</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  khajan<unclear>ā</unclear>karasa <placeName key="pl:Mahiṣa">māhisekasa</placeName> <persName key="pers:Kan-Kupana">kupanasa</persName> dāna
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>The donation of <persName key="pers:Kan-Kupana">Kupana</persName>, a citizen of Khaja in the <placeName key="pl:Mahiṣa">Mahiṣa</placeName> country.</p>
      </div>
